{"title":"How to watch the Giro d’Italia Women 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-the-giro-ditalia-women-2024","date":1720102496000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-the-giro-ditalia-women-2024\">How to watch the Giro d’Italia Women 2024</a></p>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-d-italia-women-route-live-coverage-prize-money-teams\" target=\"_blank\">Giro d’Italia Women 2024</a> will act as the meat in the women’s 2024 Grand Tour sandwich. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The race will last for eight stages. The tour begins with a time-trial in Brescia close to Lake Garda on Sunday 7th July. From there, the <em>percorso </em>moves down the boot of Italy through the Apennines towards Abruzzo where the race will finish with two tough days in the central Italian mountains on Saturday 13th and Sunday 14th July.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The reigning champion Annemiek van Vleuten will not return to defend her title following <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/annemiek-van-vleuten-interview-2024\" target=\"_blank\">her retirement at the end of 2023</a>. The title is therefore up for grabs. Lidl-Trek enter the race with a bullish lineup including <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-longo-borghini-cyclist\" target=\"_blank\">Elisa Longo Borghini </a>and Gaia Realini. Juliette Labous, the runner-up last year, will lead DSM-Firmenich-PostNL while SD Worx-Protime have Lotte Kopecky in Demi Vollering’s absence.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-longo-borghini-cyclist\">‘I hate racing for second’: Elisa Longo Borghini profile</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/pro-cycling-sponsors\">Who actually are the Tour de France team sponsors 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-balsamo-profile\">All the right moves: Elisa Balsamo profile</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-d-italia-women-route-live-coverage-prize-money-teams\">Giro d’Italia Women 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>How to watch the Giro d’Italia Women 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"654\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68c4DvXIAAqY1R-970x654.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68c4DvXIAAqY1R-970x654.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68c4DvXIAAqY1R-300x202.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68c4DvXIAAqY1R-768x518.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68c4DvXIAAqY1R-1536x1035.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68c4DvXIAAqY1R-750x506.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68c4DvXIAAqY1R-1140x768.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68c4DvXIAAqY1R.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>RCS</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 Giro d’Italia Women will be available to watch on TV with Eurosport and streaming with <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> for £6.99 per month with the basic package, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. In the United States, the same coverage will be provided on Max. In Canada, FloBikes will be streaming the race. There will also be <a href=\"https://www.giroditaliawomen.it/en/rtl-102-5/\" target=\"_blank\">radio coverage in Italian on RTL102.5</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On Eurosport and Discovery+ the race will be broadcast in Italian, English, French, German, Dutch, Spanish, Portuguese, Polish, Romanian, Czech, Serbian, Greek, Bulgarian and Turkish. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find a way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs from £5.36 per month, with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN</a></strong> </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Giro d’Italia 2024 TV and streaming times</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"654\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68epl_WEAAmqXI-970x654.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68epl_WEAAmqXI-970x654.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68epl_WEAAmqXI-300x202.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68epl_WEAAmqXI-768x518.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68epl_WEAAmqXI-1536x1035.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68epl_WEAAmqXI-750x506.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68epl_WEAAmqXI-1140x768.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/F68epl_WEAAmqXI.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>RCS</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All timings listed in BST and subject to change from the broadcasters.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Brescia – Brescia, 15.7km, ITT</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Sunday 7th July</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>11:50 – 13:50<br /><strong>Eurosport 1: </strong>17:30 – 18:30*</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Sirmione – Volta Mantovana, 110km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Monday 8th July</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 11:50 – 13:50<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 11:50 – 13:45</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Sabbioneta – Toano, 113km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Tuesday 9th July April</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 11:50 – 13:50<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 17:00 – 18:00*</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4:  Imola – Urbino, 134km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Wednesday 10th July</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 11:50 – 13:50<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 16:45 – 17:45</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Frontone – Foligno, 108km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Thursday 11th July</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 11:50 – 13:50<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 17:00 – 18:00*</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: San Benedetto del Tronto – Chieti, 159km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Friday 12th July</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 11:50 – 13:50<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 17:00 – 18:00*</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 7: Lanciano – Blockhaus, 120km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Saturday 13th July</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 11:50 – 13:50<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 17:00 – 18:00*</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 8: Pescara – L’Aquila, 117km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Sunday 14th July</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 11:50 – 13:50<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 17:15 – 18:15*</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>* Hour-long highlights packages will be available on Eurosport 1 after the conclusion of Eurosport’s coverage of the men’s Tour de France. Live broadcasting for these stages will be accessible through Discovery+ however.</em></p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-longo-borghini-cyclist\">‘I hate racing for second’: Elisa Longo Borghini profile</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/pro-cycling-sponsors\">Who actually are the Tour de France team sponsors 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n 